text:
Came in late on a business trip due to a delayed flight.  One-night stay.  Checked in the day before online with a confirmed suite night upgrade.  Got a standard room next to the elevator with dirty floors that hadn't been vacuumed.  I asked if anything else was available and was told that (1) the 28th floor was my suite night upgrade, (2) all of the rooms in the hotel are the same except for 6 suites, which were all sold out, and (3) 70% of guests are Ambassador, Titanium (where I'm at), or Platinum.

Not all bad – the good:
- Aveda bath products;
- location, next to Penn Station;
- a decent coconut and rum sorbet from the restaurant;
- and although it took 45 minutes to show up, they let me use their vacuum to clean up the room.

Skip it?
